Brunei,Resources\Primary\Palm Oil Mill Effluent,Maximum Production,"Interp(2025, 0, 2030, 0, 2035, 0, 2040, 0, 2045, 0, 2050, 0)",Tonne,,Geospatial pipeline 07_resource_potential.py Tier 2 'pome' — SRR + competing-use-fraction deducted per config.RESIDUE_RATIOS/WASTE_PARAMS,"POME OIL (recovered triglyceride, ready for biodiesel) — NOT raw POME effluent. Canonical basis per Bioenergy/Analysis/unit_conversion_anchors.md §3 + config.RESIDUE_RATIOS['pome'] note (LHV 36.5 GJ/t; LEAP Fuel-side basis). Author-side cost $225/t POME oil 2025 (collection + dewatering + triglyceride extraction + transport per Pavlenko 2019 ICCT HEFA $200-300/t mid; Loh 2013; Hayyan 2010) converted to LEAP-side TOE basis via × 0.8718 (POME-oil LHV 36.5 / TOE 41.868 — canonical guide §12.1 author-action 2026-04-29; the LEAP team's handoff used 0.86 with placeholder LHV 36 GJ/t — we use 0.8718 with the more authoritative LHV 36.5 from unit_conversion_anchors.md §3). Consumed by POME Biodiesel.",bioenergy_leap_input.csv,residue_resource,Medium,
Brunei,Resources\Primary\Palm Oil Mill Effluent,Production Cost,"Interp(2025, 196.1600, 2030, 202.1158, 2035, 208.2525, 2040, 214.5755, 2045, 221.0905, 2050, 227.8033, 2055, 234.7199, 2060, 241.8465)",2020 USD/Tonnes of Oil Equivalent,,"POME OIL (recovered triglyceride, ready for biodiesel) — NOT raw POME effluent. Canonical basis per Bioenergy/Analysis/unit_conversion_anchors.md §3 + config.RESIDUE_RATIOS['pome'] note (LHV 36.5 GJ/t; LEAP Fuel-side basis). Author-side cost $225/t POME oil 2025 (collection + dewatering + triglyceride extraction + transport per Pavlenko 2019 ICCT HEFA $200-300/t mid; Loh 2013; Hayyan 2010) converted to LEAP-side TOE basis via × 0.8718 (POME-oil LHV 36.5 / TOE 41.868 — canonical guide §12.1 author-action 2026-04-29; the LEAP team's handoff used 0.86 with placeholder LHV 36 GJ/t — we use 0.8718 with the more authoritative LHV 36.5 from unit_conversion_anchors.md §3). Consumed by POME Biodiesel.",[2026-04-29 §12.1 author-action applied] ASEAN-blended collection cost (no per-AMS variation v1); 2025 anchor compounded at 0.6%/yr (≈ +23% by 2060) to mirror ag-wage pass-through that crops carry via per_ams_feedstock_cost_panel. Branch: Resources\Primary\Palm Oil Mill Effluent,bioenergy_leap_input.csv,residue_resource,Medium,
